translated:
Landorf, Nils Theodor, physician, Gothenburg, born on January 25, 1898 in Borås to teacher Viktor Theodor L. and Alfhild Söderberg. Married in 1939 to Ingrid von Bergen. Children: Agneta born in 1940, Karin in 1942. 

Education: Graduated from Karlstad in 1918, obtained a Bachelor of Medicine from Uppsala in 1925, and a Medical License in Stockholm in 1930. 

Professional experience: Assistant at the Anatomy Institute in Uppsala, working in the histology department from 1922 to 1923. Resident physician at Söderby Hospital in 1928. Assistant and resident physician at the Surgical Department of Crown Princess Lovisa's Care Institution from 1928 to 1929. Assistant physician at Gothenburg Children's Hospital in 1930. Second Deputy Physician at the Sanatorium of the County of Västernorrland in Sundsvall from 1931 to 1932. Acting Deputy Physician at Gothenburg Children's Hospital in 1932. Assistant physician at the Medical Department there from 1932 to 1935, and Deputy Physician from 1935 to 1936. Worked at Gothenburg's Epidemic Hospital from 1936 to 1937. Established private practice as a physician in Gothenburg since 1937. Also worked as an industrial physician and physician at Gothenburg's Children's Center, school physician in the Nordhem district elementary schools and Eastern secondary school. 

Written works: Published research on pediatric topics.
